metadata.name: WHISPERS (in code) #266
metadata.description:
WHISPERS (in code) is part of the fx(hash) interactive minting experience at Performance in Code: Deciphering Value in Generative Art, Art Basel Miami Beach, 2022. 
The project is a collaborative performance between the viewer and AI. It reverses the usual approach of using AI as a tool to perform our intents (as in popular prompt-based AI methods) and gives the decision-making power to the AI, where we, humans, receive instructions on how to proceed in the creative process. Interaction happens in a multi-stage manner, in a metaphor for the process of training neural networks. At each step, after the user performs the action, they can send the image for evaluation by the neural network and receive another instruction (similarly to how networks learn by receiving feedback from the loss function).  What makes us different from the machines, however, is the presence of free will, and our ability to disobey the machine’s guidance. We are not restricted to its instructions and are free to interact with and break the artwork. 

Artwork is built on layers of photography, AI, GAN, diffusion, classification convolutional networks, random pixel manipulations, and user interaction. Like with most artist projects, it starts with a few memories, that are then re-imagined by GAN. The initial building blocks are a combination of photographs and AI outputs. The apparent lack of coherent subject choice in input images signifies how we build the perception of the world around us and apply an individual hierarchy to elements worth remembering. The blocks are then stripped of meaning by reducing them to abstract shapes and applying stochastic image transformations, guided by randomness. The neural network then learns to classify the images and outputs its best guesses on how to improve the pictures. 
 
The goal of the project is to explore the controversial question of authorship through the use of tools incorporating AI. Does it lie with decisive or executive power? Here, the boundaries are blurred and one can no longer distinguish the clear author of a finished artwork - is it the artist, AI, serendipity, or viewer? 


- Use your mouse to perform machine instructions.
- Use the "E" key to ask the neural network for instructions.
- Use the "R" key to reset the drawing.
- Use the "S" key to export an image.

metadata.name: Firework #61
metadata.description:
Welcome to "Firework," a generative art piece inspired by the beauty and significance of fireworks.

Fireworks have long been associated with celebrations and special occasions, and they are particularly well-known for their role in ringing in the new year. As we approach New Years 2023, it's a perfect time to reflect on the meaning and significance of fireworks in our culture along with our individual accomplishments made throughout this past year.

In this art piece, I aim to capture the essence of fireworks and their role in our lives. Through the use of vibrant colors, dynamic patterns, and random elements, I hope to create a sense of excitement and wonder that is evocative of the joy and wonder that fireworks bring to our celebrations.

I hope you enjoy "Firework" and that it helps you to appreciate the beauty and significance of this past year along with the coming new year.

metadata.name: Nebula, Solitude #18
metadata.description:
Nebula is one of the most magnificent stellar phenomena to behold. It is a distinct luminescent part of the interstellar medium, which consists of ionized gas and cosmic dust. Nebulae are often star-forming regions, where stars are born in solitude but surrounded by beautiful light and matter.

In this series, I continue the exploration of color and gravity, the effect of mass on speed, the effect of speed on hue, and how light can change by passing through big particles and dust systems.

I also want to let you participate in the creation of your artwork variation too. Each iteration is a unique and unpredictable dance of light in the dust and gravitation between matter clusters, however,  with the controls listed below, you can change the probability of light/dust blocks as well as the tiling layout.

[L] - create a new layout
[S] - reshuffle the current layout

[Shift] + [1] - change dust blocks probability to 0.0 and reshuffle the current layout
[Shift] + [2] - —//— 0.2
[Shift] + [3] - —//— 0.4
[Shift] + [4] - —//— 0.6
[Shift] + [5] - —//— 0.8
[Shift] + [6] - —//— 1.0

Basics:
[A] - skip/restart the animation

[1] - save PNG in low resolution
[2] - save PNG in medium resolution
[3] - save PNG in high resolution
[4] - save PNG in ultra-high resolution

Experimental zone:
[E] - toggle endless animation
[0] - save the current frame in low resolution

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.

Use Chrome 107 for the best experience, other browsers are significantly slower on this artwork, visual results also may vary.

Made with love and p5js

By Collapsar Beauty

metadata.name: glory hole$ #93
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.
